[{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"direction_paragraph\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">Write your answers in the spaces provided. Refer to the figure or diagram to answer the question. Where explanation or discussion is required, support your answers with relevant information and/or specific examples.</p><br/><div class=\"item_part part_id:ai part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"ai\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A homeowner in the Northern Hemisphere is considering installing photovoltaic (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P V\"><math alttext=\"P V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>PV</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) panels on the roof of the home to help provide electricity for the home. The homeowner has read conflicting reports on which compass direction the panels should face to maximize the amount of electricity (in <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"kilowatt hours\"><math alttext=\"kilowatt hours\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>kWh</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) that the panels can produce.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(a) The homeowner plans to design an experiment to determine the direction of the panels for maximal electricity production.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(i) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Identify</span> the independent variable in the experiment.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:aii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"aii\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(ii) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Identify</span> the dependent variable in the experiment.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:aiii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"aiii\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(iii) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Identify</span> a reasonable hypothesis for the experiment.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:aiv part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"aiv\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(iv) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Describe</span> one variable that was not discussed that could affect the results of the study.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:bi part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"bi\">\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(b) The diagram below shows another way of generating electricity using a renewable resource. The arrows indicate the flow of water.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram titled “Hydroelectric Power Generation.” The diagram displays the flow of water and how it is used to generate electricity. Water is stored on the right side of the diagram in a storage reservoir with a dam and gates near the surface and silt at the bottom. The water flows through an opening below the dam near the gates from the top right down towards the bottom left of the diagram into a turbine. The turbine is attached to a generator which is located above it inside of a powerhouse. On top of the powerhouse, a transformer is connected to power transmission cables. After the water flows through the turbine, it flows into a downstream outlet at the bottom left of the figure.\" height=\"278\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188531.g02.png\" width=\"500\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(i) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Identify</span> the location shown in the diagram where the kinetic energy of the water is transformed into mechanical energy.</p>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:bii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"bii\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(ii) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Explain</span> why the water in the storage reservoir has potential energy that is useful in hydroelectric power generation.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:biii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"biii\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(iii) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Explain</span> how coupling hydroelectric power with solar or wind power is an advantage to providing a constant source of electricity to a community.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:biv part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"biv\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(iv) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Explain</span> how a hydroelectric power system, like the one depicted, may be negatively affected by climate change.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:ci part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"ci\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(c) Over time, reservoirs that form behind dams can undergo changes.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(i) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Identify</span> one advantage, other than the generation of hydroelectric power, of the formation of a reservoir behind a hydroelectric dam.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"},{"id":"VR188531","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:cii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"cii\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(ii) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Explain</span> the effect of increased silt in the reservoir on the hydroelectric power system.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR188531_rubric"}]